                                </support>
                                <condition>An upright granite cross-slab of rectangular shape. The left edge of the slab is cracked and a section from the bottom left is missing.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>The slab is sculptured in relief on one face with a <rs type="decoration">cross</rs>. The <rs type="decoration">cross</rs> has round hollows in the angles between the arms and spiral terminations to the top and two side arms (Allen 1903, 189-90). On the left of the shaft of the <rs type="decoration">cross</rs> near the bottom is a <rs type="decoration">crescent</rs> and <rs type="decoration">V-shaped rod symbol</rs>, and on the right a <rs type="decoration">mirror-case symbol</rs>. Below these on the left a <rs type="decoration">disc</rs> and a <rs type="decoration">pair of rings symbol</rs>, and on the right a <rs type="decoration">double disc</rs> and <rs type="decoration">Z-shaped rod symbol</rs> (ibid). An ogham inscription with a drawn stem-line is incised on the left-hand-side of the slab.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
