                        <provenance type="found">The ogham was not known until recently. The first record of the inscription is an illustration from <date>2004</date> as part of the Records of the Royal Commission on the Ancient and Historical Monuments of Scotland (RCAHMS) under catalogue number <idno type="invNo">SC 1080221</idno>. The slab itself was known before <date>1822</date>, as drawn for Archaeologia Scotia volume II (Stuart 1822, 314). It likewise seems to be recorded in the Old Statistical Account volume III from <date>1792</date> (Wilson 1792, 131-2).
                        </provenance>
