            <div type="commentary">
<p>Information about the stone and its analysis is limited due to the lack of publications. However, Stevenson (1955, 126) has argued that the Dyce slab was mid- to late-ninth century based on its decoration, but this date range seems too late to Forsyth (1996, 266).</p>
